tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), indicating possible renal dysfunction and/or urinary tract pathology. HbA1c is low, which may reflect recent hypoglycemia or anemia. No evidence of infection (negative nitrite/leukocytes). Recommend further evaluation of renal function and possible underlying metabolic or urinary tract disorders.
